main event: On September 12, 1955, in Baltimore, Maryland, a civilian witnessed ten white, round objects flying in a leading line heading north for approximately 7 minutes. The objects seemed to change shape during the observation period.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 7 minutes, providing a substantial duration for observation.
The objects appeared to change shape, indicating potential unusual behavior.
The report suggests the possibility of the objects being a flight of birds, raising questions about the accuracy of the conclusion.
The witness was a 39-year-old housewife, adding credibility to the observation.
The report indicates the absence of photographs, which could have provided visual evidence of the sighting.
sighted object: Ten white, round objects in a leading line
